summaryText: The game began as a Catalan Opening: Closed, with you diverging from book at 6... O-O. White's 20. Rxa7 was a tactical miss that shifted the position to be less drawish and more dynamically sharp, while Black's 15... cxd5 was an imprecise Plan Change from Dynamic Sharpness to Pawn Storm. Black's 21... Be6 was a blunder, missing an engine-only move and facing conversion difficulties with a 24.4% best-vs-second gap. The game-changing errors occurred late: White's 23. Ra5 was a tactical miss, giving up a comfortable position, immediately followed by Black's 23... Bb6, a forced tactical miss due to a loose piece on f5, which caused a massive 87.2% drop in win probability.

20. Rxa7 is a tactical miss that significantly harms White's position, increasing Dynamic Sharpness in Black's favor. The correct move was Bc6 (pv: Bc6, Bd8, Rxa7, Re1+, Kg2, Rc8), which would have maintained control and avoided this drop in Drawishness.

Despite being a forced move, 21... Be6 is a tactical miss that dramatically reduces Black's winning chances from 80% to 38.9%. The correct move was Bb5 (pv: Bb5, Re4, Rxb7, Rxe8+, Bxe8, a4), which creates tactical opportunities, including Rxb7.

23. Ra5 is a severe tactical miss, turning a comfortable position into a losing one for White. Instead, Ba3 (pv: Ba3, Bb6, Rf4, g6, Bd5, Re2) would have maintained a strong advantage and simplified White's conversion difficulty.

sections.title: Opening Phase
sections.narrativeHint: The opening phase was characterized by White's aggressive pursuit of development and space. White quickly gained a development advantage and initiated a space grab, putting early pressure on Black's position. While the initial moves were relatively balanced, Black made a critical error at move 8...b, which significantly worsened their position and initiated a king safety crisis. Consequently, White emerged from the opening with a clear advantage.

sections.title: Tactical Complications
sections.narrativeHint: White ignited a period of profound tactical complications with their 9th move, unleashing a sequence characterized by sharp violence and dynamic piece trades. The game quickly escalated into a complex struggle, forcing both players to navigate intricate lines and a relentless 'squeeze'. This intense tactical storm demanded absolute precision, maintaining high tension throughout the ply range.

sections.title: Tactical Complications
sections.narrativeHint: White plunged the position into a maelstrom of tactical complications, initiating a sequence marked by fierce violence and extensive piece trades. This intense period demanded precise calculation, with both sides navigating a perilous landscape where even subtle moves led to significant evaluation drops. The sheer complexity of the lines made accurate play exceedingly difficult, transforming the board into a tactical minefield.

sections.title: Critical Turning Point
sections.narrativeHint: The game reached a critical turning point at move 20.w, where White committed a severe blunder, dropping their evaluation by a staggering 30.1%. This decisive error immediately swung the momentum, plunging White into a precarious position that ignited a period of intense tactical exchanges and material adjustments. Though Black later faltered slightly at move 22...b, failing to fully capitalize, White's initial misstep irrevocably altered the game's trajectory into a volatile and desperate struggle.
